news.title: CIDCO launches mass housing scheme in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Maharashtra Urban Development Minister Eknath Shinde said the CIDCO housing scheme was gaining popularity due to its quality construction, affordable rates and transparent online processing.

news.title: Builders requests Telangana government to reconsider hike in property registration charges
news.para: Telangana government is mulling hiking registration charges – by 20% to 50% depending on the nature of the property – beginning next month. Earlier in July 2021, the state had revised the registration costs apart from increasing the stamp duty from 6% to 7.5%.

news.title: Builders request Maharashtra government not to raise RR rates, expect boosters
news.para: The property registration department has started discussions on the division-wise revision of the Ready Reckoner (RR) rates, which are announced in April every year. There was no revision in the rates due to the pandemic last year. Tthere was a slight increase (1.74%) in the rates announced in September 2020.

news.title: UP-RERA fines seven builders over Rs 1 crore for not handing over flats within deadline
news.para: All the seven builders have failed to deliver the units to their buyers within the stipulated deadlines. While four have projects in Noida, two are from Ghaziabad and one is based in Meerut.

news.title: Home First Finance posts net profit of Rs 46 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income during October-December 2021 rose over 37 per cent to Rs 152 crore from Rs 110 crore, while the asset under management (AUM) has crossed Rs 5,000 crore in January 2022, it added.

news.title: HSIL's profit down 21% to Rs 29 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: HSIL's revenue from operation was higher at Rs 638.75 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 541.48 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's profit up 6% to Rs 767.33 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: "Even the provisions were less in the quarter because of the provisions we had made earlier," LIC Housing's Managing Director and CEO Y Viswanatha Gowd said.

news.title: NCLAT asks DHFL lenders to reconsider resolution plan on avoidable transactions valuation aspect
news.para: ​Under the insolvency resolution proceedings for the crisis-hit DHFL, Piramal Capital had emerged as the winning bidder and the Committee of Creditors (CoC) had ascribed a value of just Re 1 for Rs 45,000 crore-worth recoverable assets of DHFL. These were assets apparently diverted fraudulently by the erstwhile promoters of DHFL.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit declines 59.2% to Rs 73 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Dalmia Bharat's revenue from operations was almost flat at Rs 2,731 crore during the quarter under review, compared with Rs 2,737 crore a year ago.

news.title: HC reserves order on Ansals plea to suspend seven-year jail term in Uphaar case
news.para: ​Justice Subramonium Prasad heard the arguments on behalf of counsel for Ansals, another convicted person Anoop Singh Karayat, Delhi Police, and Association of the Victims of Uphaar Tragedy (AVUT).

news.title: Macrotech has managed to pull off deleveraging as well as a growth story: Abhishek Lodha
news.para: “Ours is a deleveraging cum growth story which is not easy to pull off but we find that we are able to deliver on both fronts. Our cost of debt has moderated by 120 bps or 1.2% over the last nine months and we expect this to significantly fall going forward.”

news.title: India initiates anti-dumping probe against imports of vinyl tiles from China, Taiwan, Vietnam
news.para: Welspun India Ltd, Welspun Flooring Ltd and Welspun Global Brands Ltd had filed a petition before the directorate to impose anti-dumping duty on the imports from China, Taiwan and Vietnam, according to a notification of the DGTR.

news.title: Two Greater Noida housing societies penalized over waste management
news.para: The action was taken on instructions of GNIDA CEO Narendra Bhooshan against Galaxy North Avenue and Victory One Amayra societies in Greater Noida (West) which have been slapped with Rs 40,400 and Rs 10,200 penalties, respectively, it said.

news.title: ED arrests Karvy stock broking CMD & CFO in money laundering case
news.para: ​The agency produced the two-- already lodged in central jail, Bengaluru after being arrested by the police-- before a special Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) court in Hyderabad on January 20 and on January 25 it remanded them to four days of ED custody from January 27-30, it said in a statement.

news.title: China property shares slump as planned U.S. rate hike adds to woes
news.para: Regulatory curbs on borrowing have driven China's property sector into crisis, highlighted by Evergrande, the world's most indebted property firm. The contagion has engulfed other Chinese developers, roiled global financial markets in the past year and contributed to a slump in China's property market, which accounts for a quarter of its economy.
